{
  "texts": [
    "Logically, the aforementioned prompt assigns two tasks to the LLM, including what optimization to do and how to do it.",
    "However, previous studies [63] show that splitting the tasks into small pieces and guiding the LLM step by step maximizes the ability of the LLM.",
    "Our experimental results in Section V-E also conform this argument.",
    "(ii) Various optimizations cannot help each other, which limits the optimization effect.",
    "The aforementioned one-shot use compresses various optimizations into one interaction with the LLM, eliminating the possibility of different optimizations helping each other."
  ]
}